### CSS Outline

**Outline** is a line drawn **outside** the border, but **inside** the margin.

---

### Key Differences from Border

| Feature | Border | Outline |
|---------|--------|---------|
| Part of box model | Yes | No |
| Affects layout | Yes (adds to size) | No |
| Per-side styling | Yes | No (always all sides) |
| Border-radius | Affected | Not affected |
| Use case | Decorative lines | Focus indicators |

---

### Outline Properties

```css
/* Width */
outline-width: 2px;
outline-width: thin | medium | thick;

/* Style */
outline-style: solid | dashed | dotted | double | none;

/* Color */
outline-color: red;
outline-color: invert; /* Inverts background */

/* Shorthand */
outline: 2px solid blue;
```

---

### Outline Offset

```css
/* Gap between border and outline */
outline-offset: 3px;
outline-offset: -2px; /* Inside the border */
```

---

### Focus Outline

```css
/* Default focus outline */
input:focus {
  outline: 2px solid blue;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* Custom focus ring */
button:focus-visible {
  outline: 3px solid #4299e1;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* Remove default outline (DO with custom focus style) */
button:focus {
  outline: none;
  /* Always provide alternative focus style */
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(66, 153, 225, 0.5);
}
```

---

### Outline vs Box Shadow for Focus

```css
/* Outline focus - works in high contrast mode */
.focus-outline:focus {
  outline: 3px solid blue;
}

/* Box shadow focus - more visually appealing */
.focus-shadow:focus {
  outline: none;
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px blue;
}

/* Combined approach */
.focus-combined:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid blue;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

---

### Accessibility Note

Never remove `outline` without providing a visible focus indicator. Keyboard users rely on focus outlines to navigate.

> **Best Practice:** Use outline for focus indicators. Use `outline: none` ONLY when replacing with a visible alternative like `box-shadow` or a custom focus ring.
